Jim's is a Buffalo phenomenon not to be missed.  This location has limited seating (bar stools facing the wall) but the food is great.  The menu is extensive, so same time and money and just ask for the sub of the week or if you're really hungry, get the combo so you get to have their amazing fries.  They also have a 15% Veteran's discount, though sometimes they have to be reminded of it.

I was taken back and bothered at how disrespectful this guy was being. This was the first time in my life that I walked into an establishment and was told that I was not welcomed to eat there. It's not a great feeling especially when you did nothing wrong. Then I tried calling to speak to a manager but the same employee was being rude and just kept hanging up on me. Their excuse was there are a lot of bars around and they deal with a lot of drunk people. I guess everyone that laughs is clearly drunk. I think corporate should come up with a better method for training their employees when it comes to customer service because what ever they're doing now, is clearly not working. You were completely unprofessional and left a bad taste in my mouth. I truly hope you change because it seems like people really enjoy your product.
